    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-05-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-05-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="665"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d665">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Williams</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Rockhill</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">United States Consulate-General</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-05-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 11, 1896</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 2968.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I beg to acknowledge the receipt of the
                    Department’s telegram of the 9th instant. * * *</p>
                <p>In consequence I addressed a communication to the governor and captain-general in
                    the same sense almost word for word.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ramon O. Williams.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
